benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/search/{searchKey} - Search custom fields

covered: Valid Request scenarios are well represented by multiple happy-path and parameterized tests (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC12, TC14, TC15, TC16, TC17, TC18, TC19, TC20, TC22, TC23, TC24, TC25, TC26, TC27, TC28, TC29, TC30).

Query Parameters tested extensively (limit, offset, audit, extra, malformed, negative, missing, invalid values) across multiple test cases (TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11, TC12, TC13, TC14, TC15, TC16, TC18, TC28, TC29).
Pagination handling tested (limit/offset with multiple scenarios, including boundary limits and empty pages) (TC02, TC07, TC09, TC28).
Authorization scenarios covered (missing token, invalid token) (TC15, TC16).
Error handling scenarios covered (400 for invalid inputs; 503 for service unavailability; 405 for invalid method; 401 for authentication failures) (TC11, TC12, TC13, TC14, TC15, TC16, TC17, TC30).
Backward compatibility and integration aspects touched (TC22, TC23).
XSS/injection and input validation considerations (TC18, TC25, TC27).
Performance-related acceptance (TC19, TC20) including stress and concurrency concepts.
gaps: Rate limiting tests are not explicitly present (guideline mentions rate limiting as a concern).
Caching behavior tests (ETag, Cache-Control headers) are not covered.
Explicit 403/authorization failure scenarios beyond 401 (e.g., insufficient permissions) are not depicted.
Detailed validation of error response formatting and accessibility for all error codes could be more explicit (beyond status codes).
recommendations: Add explicit tests for rate limiting/throttling behavior (e.g., multiple rapid requests and429 handling if applicable).
Add caching header validation tests (ETag/Cache-Control) and ensure consistent caching behavior across responses.
Include a scenario for 403 Forbidden if a user is authenticated but lacks required permissions, to complement 401 tests.
Enhance error response validation to assert on structure and accessibility guidelines for all error cases (beyond HTTP status codes).
Consider a dedicated test verifying behavior when required path parameter is missing or empty string is supplied (edge case robustness).
